<item>
            <title>[LANG-494] CharSet sub-classes cannot be made thread-safe</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LANG-494</link>
                <project id="12310481" key="LANG">Commons Lang</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;AFAICT, CharSet sub-classes cannot be made thread-safe.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is because the HashMap and HashSet collections are not thread-safe.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If a sub-class updates COMMON, there is no guarantee that getInstance() will see the update.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the case of the instance variable &quot;set&quot;, the sub-class could override all the read/write methods to provide thread-safety.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
